5000|$|And they which hold in <b>frank-almoign</b> {{are bound}} of right before God to make orisons, prayers, masses, and other divine services, for {{the souls of}} their grantor or feoffor, and for the souls of their {{ancestors}} which are dead, and for the prosperity and good life and good health of their heirs, which are alive. And therefore they shall do no fealty to their lord ... because, that this divine service is better for them before God, than any doing of fealty; and also because that these words (<b>frank-almoign)</b> exclude the lord to have any earthly or temporal service, but to have only divine and spiritual service {{to be done for}} him, &c.|$|E

